How exactly the model works, see the description of the version.

I was very meticulous in my choice of photographs. Each film has its own nuances. But film is only part of the success of good photography. At some point, I had a problem with the fact that the camera had a much stronger influence on the final result than the film. All models are united by style, a variety of photos, portraits of people, landscapes, night views of the city or underwater shooting were used for training.

My thanks -

XpucT for the excellent Reliberate model used for training.

Lomography.com for a great photo database.

items.name: Jean Grey (X-Men) LoRA
items.description:
One of my least favorite characters but I made a LoRA anyway. This does not depict her movie/tv show appearances, only comic.

Basics

  • Best used at strengths of 0.6 - 1.

  • Activation tag is "jean-grey" followed by "green bodysuit" or "red bodysuit" for the different Phoenix costumes. Add "gloves" and "sash" for more accuracy if needed.

  • Also her classic Marvel Girl outfit is included if you use "green dress, mask, cleavage, belt." I would have made a custom tag for this but I wanted to test it without it then didn't feel like going back and rerunning the stuff blah blah. Will fix this if I update.

Issues

  • The LoRA is heavily biased towards her phoenix chest emblem and is difficult to get rid of unless you put her in outfits that have a wide collar.

  • The LoRA is also biased towards fire effects and, depending on the checkpoint, warmer lighting. These can disappear at lower strengths and/or with negative prompts.

  • The mask may fuse to her nose and cheeks and may need light sketching to fill in the holes.

This Lora was made purely for a fun and self-learning experiences. I DID NOT INTEND and DO NOT give permissions for this LoRA to be used for any commercial/promotional/financial gain uses.

items.name: Tangbohu buff effector 唐伯虎效果增益巴福
items.description:
Tangbohu buff effector

It is a very interesting little toy that can enhance the details of the screen and provide more fun

Different weights will cause different things to happen

A weight of 0 is definitely not recommended, as it will damage the image and turn it into something strange

The image with a weight between 0.1 and 1 will attempt to be split into multiple parts, with multiple characters appearing, and may also exist as various small characters such as picture frames

Weight>1<2, the image returns to a whole block and adds more details, resulting in higher saturation

When the weight>2, the screen starts to lose control, and the character's face may show some unnecessary details

Anyway, it's just fun,

Tangbohu buff effector

是一个非常有意思的小玩具，他能够增强画面的细节，提供更多的乐趣

不同的权重会发生不同的事情

权重为0绝对不推荐，会破坏画面变成奇奇怪怪的东西

权重0.1-1之间画面会尝试分割成多份出现多个人物，也有可能以画框等各种小人存在

权重>1 <2画面回归一整块并且添加了更多的细节，饱和度也更高

权重>2 画面开始失控人物脸部会出现一些不需要的细节

总之就是很好玩，可以试一下

I went down to South Park and created a LoRA out of the art style!

Recommended settings:

If you want an adult version of the South Park characters, type in the words "tall" and/or "adult", and the model should be giving you the adult model more accurately.

LoRA weight: ~0.5-0.6

It's optional, but just in case, if your images result in a realistic photo, just add the words:

cartoon, south park style

Checkpoints: I recommend Deliberate, since I mostly tested the images on it.

Negative prompt that works well:

deformed, bad anatomy, disfigured, poorly drawn face, mutation, mutated, extra limb, ugly, disgusting, poorly drawn hands, missing limb, floating limbs, disconnected limbs, malformed hands, blurry, ((mutated hands and fingers)), duplicate images, duplicate, (deformed, distorted, disfigured:1.3), poorly drawn, bad anatomy, wrong anatomy, extra limb, missing limb, floating limbs, (mutated hands and fingers:1.4), disconnected limbs, mutation, mutated, ugly, disgusting, blurry, amputation, EasyNegative, ng_deepnegative_v1_75t

DeepNegative and EasyNegative are very recommended.

This is only the first version, and I will iron out any problems in the next ones.

Suggestions and feedback are welcome! I hope you enjoy

items.name: Retro Big Naturals - Photorealistic Natural Boobs
items.description:
• Big boobs? Check.

  • Natural boobs? Check.

  • Retro styling? Check

This LoRA is trained on retro imagery of big natural breasts and women. It produces images that tend to favor an "old school" style of natural women -- it does big boobs, but they're natural and trained on more natural bodies. It also tends to favor pubic hair, and natural tanning (read: tan lines). It also favors a photographic style that's film based, grainier, and overall more of a retro style.

This LoRA has been heavily baked. I recommend using it at 0.7 -- it'll definitely artifact up higher. And it's fine at 0.4-0.6 as well.

Most realistic models tend to work OK, but gotta say that Art + Eros tribute seems to really jive with this LoRA.

The keyword isn't required at all, but you may find that using the retrobigguns keyword helps here and again.

Depending on your taste, but I have to say that the prompt word thicc seems to work awesome with this one. Bigger boobs usually means bigger women, and they fit so well and look better. But, to each their own, you do you.

I'm still working through my training procedures, so, hopefully get some v2's of the LoRA's I have up soon, but in the meanwhile my best procedure is to overbake somewhat and then reduce the weights. So, if you set the weight too high, prepare for it to be deep fried.

items.name: Stripey Thigh-High Socks LoRA
items.description:
Everybody loves striped thigh high socks, right? Unfortunately, I found a great number of the excellent checkpoints on this site have a devil of a time rendering actual stripes on stockings. So, I made this LoRA to try and fix that. This is just the version 1 of this. I am sure I will come back later, do another version and maybe even combine versions 1 and 2 for a super-LoRA!

Trigger word is stripedsocks. I recommend using "[color1] striped socks" where color1 is whatever color you want. Usually, with that prompt, the models will do Color + White stripes. If you do "[Color 1] and [Color 2] striped socks", that works about 80% of the time. If you go with three or more colors, though, the patterning goes all weird and you get what you get.

I have tested with several different models and it worked well with each. Recommend a strength of 0.75-1.

items.name: M.OS Realistic Diffusion
items.description:
Motivation

As a 3D generalist and CGI artist, I often find myself in the need of complex and specific moodboards, and, if you ever did one, you most certainly know that this is almost impossible. Pinterest, ArtStation, Behance, and general Google Search can get you only as far as someone already imagined - so the inspiration is either limited or unconsistent.

This makes my take on AI art too: a huge oasis of unlimited moodboards customized and fine-tuned my your own need. But for this tool to really do wonders and to be a trusty sidekick even in a production environment, a lot of tweaking is required.

M.OS Realistic Diffusion aims to be the fine-tuned model that can be used by artists of various industries to kickstart their creations even if they work in automotive, photography, game, fashion, or architecture.

The Model

... is trained using CC0 libraries, stock images, and my own copyrighted work.

Recommended settings:

  • Clip Skip 2;

  • VAE: StabilityAI ft-MSE 850000 EMA (How to);

  • Dynamic Thresholding (more samples and details without clipping);

  • Hires. Fix (for weird aspect ratios);

  • Optimized for 512px and 768px;

  • Sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras;

  • Soft / cinematic looks: 2-6 CFG + 10-20 Steps (fast);

  • Realistic looks: 6-10 CFG + 20-40 Steps (balanced);

  • Dramatic / high-detail looks: >10 CFG + >40 Steps (slower);

Samplers (based on no. of samples required to produce good images, in order - CFG 7):

  • Fast (<10 steps): DPM++ SDE Karras, Euler, Euler a, DPM ++ SDE, DDIM;

  • Balanced (<20 steps): DPM++ 2M, DPM++ 2M Karras, Heun;

  • Slow (<30 steps): DPM++ 2M SDE Karras, PLMS, LMS.

Take a moment to leave a rating and fav. M.OS Realistic Diffusion. It will give me a greater chance to reach a broader audience and fine-tune the model further.

Resolution: 512x768

Lora strength: 0.7-0.8

Instance Token: petemoh

His art style is of fantasy themed creatures, so keep that in mind when building your prompt.

Good starting prompts:

oil painting \(medium\),

faceless, mask, monster, jewelry, armor,

monster, creature, wings, horror \(theme\), gothic

You can try mix-matching these to see the different results.

A lot of the backgrounds consisted of cloudy skies so be specific about what type of background you want. If you want to minimize the clouds, put that in the negative prompt.

Also, most of the images were of men, so if you want females you need to put a higher emphasis on prompts like 1girl -> (1girl:1.4), and set things like 1boy in the negative prompt.

items.name: Western Animation Diffusion
items.description:
Western Animation Diffusion

Comicbook and Western Animation Style Model

Do you like what I do? Consider supporting me on Patreon 🅿️ or feel free to buy me a coffee ☕.
A ❤️, a kind comment or a review is greatly appreciated.

Purpose of this model

  • Train character loras where the dataset is mostly made of cartoon screencaps or comicbooks, allowing less style transfer and less overfitting.

  • Add variety to mixes.

  • Have an alternative to anime models when it comes to western stuff.

  • Not for western style lora training. Pretty good when used with western style loras (thanks @AnteMaxx), but needs weight adjusting, as it's already closer to the lora style probably.

Suggested settings

  • Set the ETA Noise Seed Delta (ENSD) to 31337

  • Set CLIP Skip to 2

  • DISABLE face restore. It's terrible, never use it

  • Use negative prompts and embeddings that don't ruin the style

  • Use AnimeVideo or Foolhardy as upscalers in highres fix

  • Use ADetailer for far away shots or full body images to avoid blurred faces

Brief history

This was requested by a supporter and I also wanted to see if I was capable of doing it. It was a funny little project.

The Batmobile's shields are made of ceramic fractal armor panels. They explode outward when struck by projectiles, deflecting injurious force away from the car and its occupants. If Batman must leave the Batmobile for an extended period of time, he can, through a voice command spoken into a wrist device (specifically, the word "shields"), activate the Batmobile's shielding system. While this armor is in place, the vehicle cannot be driven. Spherical bombs could be deployed from its sides. An afterburner was housed in the back. Its grappling hook, once hooked on a structure, serves as an anchor to allow the batmobile to make an extremely sharp turn at high speed that its pursuers typically cannot duplicate. items.name: Disco Delirium (SDXL Update!)
items.description:
A Disco Elysium inspired LoRA using over a hundred images.


Model Information:

Primarily trained on portraits, this LoRA is fantastic at character generations, and mixes incredibly well with other styles. Includes version for SD1.5 and SDXL 1.0

How to use:

This LoRA has been trained on several varieties of prompt, but I've personally found best results using a [subject], [pose], [details], [style/lighting] style prompt. Prompts should be prefaced with "disco elysium" as an activation token.

Model works well with a variety of CFG scales, but lower (4.5-6) values are needed to bring out some of the artistic flourishes as seen in the game.

New lora from kate from shadows house, this lora was trained with 50 images using the anything v5 model, the weight I recommend is 0.7 to 1.

add "black silhouette" and "silhouette" to your prompts for better results

please leave me your comments and generations.

without more to write, enjoy it!

Stealth mode avoids detection using a variety of stealth technologies that reduce reflection/emission of radar, infrared, visible light, radio-frequency spectrum, and audio; the car's lights and main engine are deactivated; the vehicle is powered by an auxiliary electric motor. This makes the car very hard to find at night or in dark places and can easily throw off pursuers.
